div.p:
The founts in use in English printing-offices may be divided into two kinds;
                    those used for hook, and those for job printing, that is, hand and posting
                    bills, &c. Of book types there are twelve regular bodies, viz. Great Primer,
                    English, Pica, Small Pica, Long Primer, Bourgeois, Brevier, Minion, Nonpareil,
                    Ruby, Pearl, and Diamond. Besides these, Minion-Nonpareil is a good deal used;
                    and some founders have introduced intermediate founts, as Emerald.
